<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tool on Saitech</title><link>https://saitech.blog/tags/tool/</link><description>Recent content in Tool on Saitech</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 26 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://saitech.blog/tags/tool/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Flameshot broken with the new update</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/flameshot-broken-with-the-new-update/</link><pubDate>Tue, 26 Aug 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/flameshot-broken-with-the-new-update/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/flameshot-broken-with-the-new-update/1.png" alt="Featured image of post Flameshot broken with the new update" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;The latest version of &lt;code&gt;Flameshot&lt;/code&gt; on Arch Linux is broken, it messes up the resolution, causes distortion in the resulting image, and makes the fonts unreadable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The solution? Roll back to an earlier version. And since Iâ€™m lazy, Iâ€™ll just write it down here: how to do it, and which version worked for me, so that next time I run into this Iâ€™ll know exactly which one to go back to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="remove-flameshot"&gt;Remove Flameshot
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -Rns flameshot
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="downgrade"&gt;Downgrade
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id="using-arch-linux-archive-ala"&gt;Using Arch Linux Archive (ALA)
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id="remove-flameshot-1"&gt;Remove Flameshot
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/f/flameshot/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/f/flameshot/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4 id="download-it"&gt;Download it
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;wget https://archive.archlinux.org/packages/f/flameshot/flameshot-13.0.1-1-x86
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id="install-manually"&gt;Install manually
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo pacman -U flameshot-13.0.1-1-x86_64.pkg.tar.zst
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="using-the-downgrade-tool"&gt;Using the downgrade tool
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id="install-downgrade"&gt;Install downgrade
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;YAY -S downgrade
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4 id="run-downgrade"&gt;Run downgrade
&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sudo downgrade flameshot
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the menu, pick version &lt;strong&gt;13.0.1&lt;/strong&gt; and youâ€™re done.
Using the downgrade tool is definitely more convenient, but remember itâ€™s still another piece of software you need to trust and keep an eye on.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Converting Image to ASCII</title><link>https://saitech.blog/p/converting-image-to-ascii/</link><pubDate>Thu, 10 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://saitech.blog/p/converting-image-to-ascii/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://saitech.blog/p/converting-image-to-ascii/33.png" alt="Featured image of post Converting Image to ASCII" /&gt;&lt;p&gt;Simple local guide on how to install a program to convert images to ASCII art.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can find all instructions here.&lt;/p&gt;
